  title `Short title and extend`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00009_194715_1517807322354&sectionId=31522&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00009_194715_1517807322354
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * This Act may be called the Armed Forces (Emergency Duties)`
  line `Act, 1947.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The brackets and figure "(1)" omitted by Act 4 of 1948, s. 2.`
  line
  line `2. Omitted by s. 2, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (31523)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Emergency duties of Armed Forces`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00009_194715_1517807322354&sectionId=31523&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00009_194715_1517807322354
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, declare any specified service ^1[in a State] to be a service of vital importance to the`
  line `community:`
  line
  line `Provided that such notification shall remain in force for one month in the first instance, but may be`
  line `extended, from time to time, by a like notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon a declaration being made under sub-section (1) and until it is rescinded, it shall be the duty`
  line `of every person subject to ^2[the Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950) or the Air Force Act, 1950 (45 of 1950)],`
  line `or ^3* * * ^4[the Navy Act, 1957 (62 of 1957)], to obey any command given by any superior officer in`
  line `relation to employment upon or in connection with the service specified in the declaration; and every such`
  line `command shall be deemed to be a lawful command within the meaning and for the purposes of the`
  line `said Acts.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "in a Part A State or a Part C State or, if so requested by the Government of`
  line `a Part B State any specified service in that State".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3 and the Schedule, ibid., for "the Indian Army Act, 1911, or the Indian Air Force Act, 1932".`
  line
  line `3. The words "the Naval Discipline Act, in the form in which it is set forth in the First Schedule to" omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 58 of 1960, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "the Indian Navy (Discipline) Act, 1934".`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (31524)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Validation of certain past commands.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00009_194715_1517807322354&sectionId=31524&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00009_194715_1517807322354
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Every command given, alter the 30th day of September,`
  line `1946, and before the commencement of this Act, to any person referred to in sub-section (2) of section 2`
  line `by any superior officer in relation to employment upon or in connection with any such service as the`
  line `central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in his behalf, shall be deemed to`
  line `have been a lawful command within the meaning and for the purposes of the Acts referred to in that`
  line `sub-section, so, however, that no such person shall be punished by reason only of his not having obeyed`
  line `any such command.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
